FT  15 APR 93 / UK Company News: Whitecroft sells Wallcote companies
Whitecroft, the building products, lighting and textiles company, has sold
its Wallcote subsidiaries and has now largely withdrawn from home
improvement activities.
Purchaser was Wallcote Group, a company set up for the purpose of the
acquisition by Mr Barry Beck, managing director and one of the founders of
the business.
